    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="565"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13840: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jarvis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-28T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 28, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 28—2:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My December 26, 5 p.m. Seventh Day Adventist Mission at Sining, Chinghai, has
                    telegraphed me that the local government is loyal, the situation is quiet and
                    evacuation is difficult owing to lack of facilities.</p>
                <p>2. I telegraphed yesterday to missions in Chinghai and Kansu (except Pingliang)
                    that the situation had eased and to advise Americans to use their own discretion
                    in the light of local conditions.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Peiping, Nanking, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jarvis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
